Atomic Energy of Canada Limited is a Canadian federal Crown corporation and Canada’s largest nuclear science and technology laboratory. AECL developed the CANDU reactor technology starting in the 1950s, and in October 2011 licensed this technology to Candu Energy. Today AECL develops peaceful applications from nuclear technology through expertise in physics, metallurgy, chemistry, biology and engineering. AECL’s activities range from research and development, design and engineering to specialized technology development, waste management and decommissioning.
